DEPLOYMENT NOTE
Evaluation or use of a cryptographic reference implementation does not
replace independent cryptanalytic review, formal verification, or
deployment-specific security engineering. The formal results are stated
for the ciphertext-only, single-key-epoch model; under known plaintext the
boundary of Section 16 of the paper applies. Production deployment therefore
requires the Rev 4.0 Enqpy-HKU profile (Section 17 of the paper / FCD 8.10):
fresh external-entropy key-epoch rotation before that boundary, encrypt-then-MAC
authentication, nonce-uniqueness infrastructure, secure key storage,
constant-time MOD16 table lookups, and secure erase of key material.
